title: 187th
desc: Song recorded in 1996 for Kanye's rap group The Chicago Outfit (later known as The Go Getters). Song was posted by GLC to his blog in 2009.

title: A Step Back
desc: Song from the 1990s with Kanye's first rap group State of Mind. Likely from the early 1990s as most State of Mind songs.

title: Baby's Coming

title: Dream Come True [V1]
desc: Early demo of "All Falls Down" with alternate lyrics, hook, and an entirely new beat. Nearly a completly different song.

title: Ever Since
desc: Recorded in 1998, leaked in 2008, full version has not currently been found.

title: Family Business
desc: Original version of Family Business found on the 2001 demo tape. Kanye's voice is used as a reference for the sample chop.

title: Freestyle
desc: Track 13 off of the 2001 demo tape.

title: Gotta Pose
desc: Track 7 off of the 2001 demo tape.

title: Have It Your Way
desc: Track 3 off of the 2001 demo tape.

title: Hey Mama [V1]

title: Home (Windy)
desc: Original version of "Home" featured on the 2001 demo tape as track 1.

title: Jesus Walks [V2]

title: Know The Game
desc: Track 10 off of the 2001 demo tape.

title: Last Freestyle

title: Motherfucker [V1]

desc: Second version of "Motherfucker" with Smoke & Numbers. Was lost for awhile before being rediscovered by Batby.

desc: Song featured on the leaked demo tape from 2001. A higher quality version than this version is available.

title: Never Lettin' Go (The Stalker Song) [V2]
desc: Higher quality version of V1, however it has a producer tag at the beginning which is missing from the version on the demo tape.

title: Nothing's Gonna Stop Me
desc: Regular throwaway track around the time of The Go Getters, samples Marilyn McCoo and Billy Davis, Jr.'s "Nothing Can Stop Me"

title: Out Of Your Mind [V1]
desc: Early version of the song "Out Of Your Mind" that does not feature any vocals from John Legend. Was included in the 2001 demo tape commonly known as The Prerequisite.

title: Payback
feat: (feat. Sly Paranoid & Timmy G) (prod. Brian "Allday" Miller)
desc: Unreleased song that leaked in 2008.

title: Roommates
desc: Made in 1996 and rumoured to be one of his first songs.

title: Weak Azz Producer
desc: Very short track without a beat.

title: Wow
desc: Original version of "Wow" featuring an extra third verse. Track 5 off of the 2001 demo tape. Mentioned on "Last Call".

title: Ya Feel
desc: Leaked in Nov 2017 by garetare from the Kanye + GG tape. Made around 2000.

title: You're My Type
desc: Found on a fake mixtape, never officially released.

title: Lupe Fiasco - Birds & The Bees
desc: Early Lupe song produced by Kanye, one of the oldest colaborations between the two if not the first, its possible Kanye and Lupe had already met before the making of this track. Kanye has vocals in the intro. Recorded in 2001.

title: Mikkey Halsted - Ghetto Life
desc: Unreleased Mikkey Halsted track, produced by Kanye. Was on a scrapped Mikkey Halsted album.

title: Myleka - Candy
desc: Unreleased Myleka song "Candy" featuring Kanye.

title: Ol' Dirty Bastard - Keep The Receipt
desc: Includes an unreleased verse, different intro and new ad-libs.

desc: A very early version of The College Dropout that is composed of 15 tracks and 2 bonus tracks. Most of the songs were took off the project. Likely early/mid 2003, since only a few songs were worked on further and there are a lot of instrumental tracks. Most of these songs found its way into the fan mixtapes series The Freshmen Adjustment.

desc: Early copy leaked before the official release, featuring only 15 tracks.

title: Arguing [V2]
desc: Version of "Arguing" that was included on the unofficial mixtape Freshmen Adjustment under the name "Out Of Your Mind". Very similar to the previous version however there are John Legend vocals over the Martin Lawrence sample.

title: Breathe In Breathe Out
desc: Original version with the hook sung by Kanye instead of Ludacris.

title: Drug Dealin'
desc: Original version of "We Don't Care" which features rougher vocals, additional vocals by Keyshia Cole and a verse from GLC.

title: Get Em High [V1]
desc: Version of "Get Em High" with only a Common feature, apparently made before Talib Kweli recorded his verse. Seems to have open section for Talib.

title: Get Em High [V2]
desc: Early version of "Get Em High" with a different vocal take, worse mixing and no Common verse.

title: Hey Mama [V2]
desc: OG version with multiple unheard adlibs, poor mixing, beat switchesand a different vocal take.

title: I Need To Know [V2]
desc: Version of "I Need To Know" that contains elements of the version of the demo tape and the version used in the unofficial mixtape "Freshmen Adjustment". Uses a different vocal take than both versions. Was likely included in some mixtape as the beginning has a DJ talking and at the end it seems to transition into another song. Unknown if the unedited version is in circulation.

title: I Need To Know [V3]
desc: Later version of "I Need To Know" which was featured on early versions of The College Dropout. Sounds more finished than the previous version.

title: Improvise
desc: Song that was featured on early versions of The College Dropout. Commonly known as "Apologize" due to it beng named that on the popular unofficial mixtape Freshmen Adjustment.

title: Intro
desc: OG version of "intro" with an entirely new skit.

title: Jesus Walks Intro
desc: Song from an early copy of The College Dropout.

title: Jesus Walks [V3]
desc: An original version of "Jesus Walks" with a Rhymefest verse.

title: Livin' A Movie Pt. 1
desc: Featured on early versions of The College Dropout. In the song Kanye mentions that "this only part 1". Was included on the popular unofficial mixtape Freshmen Adjustment.

title: Livin' A Movie Pt. 2
desc: Part 2 of the song with a different beat and bars than part 1. Only a video of Kanye playing the song in the studio exists. Lyrics from part 2 are referenced in part 1.

title: Never Let Me Down
desc: Original version with early vocals and production.

title: Peace [V1]
desc: Version of "Peace" that is shorter, has an earlier vocal take and less backing vocals.

title: Peace [V2]
desc: Song featured on early versions of The College Dropout. Was included on the unofficial mixtape Freshmen Adjustment under the name "Doing Fine", however this is not confirmed to be the official name. The official name is likely either "Peace" or "Whole Life". Features background vocals from an unknown vocalist.

title: Slow Jamz
desc: Original version with early vocals and a longer bridge.

title: Two Words [V1]
desc: Solo version of "Two Words" sold by Iceman.

title: Two Words [V2]
desc: An early demo of "Two Words".

title: Bittersweet [V1]
desc: Made 13/02/2004 (According to date in MTV "Bittersweet" Preview). One of the first songs made for Late Registration but was cut due to it not coinciding well into the "overall landscape" . This version has no flute and slightly different drums. Audio comes from an MTV preview talking about the making of the song with Kanye and John Mayer.

title: Bittersweet [V2]
desc: Original version of "Bittersweet Poetry". Very similar to V1, but with flute and different mixing.

title: Celebration
desc: An early version of the instrumentals and lyrics performed live.

title: Crack Music [V1]
desc: Kanye's verses only.

title: Diamonds From Sierra Leone
desc: Snippet featuring alternate bars and a different beat. Unknown where this audio came from.

title: Gone
desc: Version of a song that features a Rhymefest verse, not seen in the release version.

title: Hey Mama [V3]
desc: Version of the song that features a different mix than the final.

title: Promised Land Pt.1
desc: Skit that is track 1 on an early version of a Late Registration tracklist. Later retooled and put on Malik Yusef's album G.O.O.D. Morning, G.O.O.D. Night: Dawn with an Adam Levine feature.

title: Touch It
desc: Rough unfinished demo. Rumored to be intended for Common and Ludacris. Pusha T later rapped on the beat on his Fear of God mixtape.

title: Touch The Sky
desc: Original version of "Touch The Sky" with no Lupe Fiasco, drums by Questlove, and Robert Glasper doing piano on the outro. Played by Just Blaze on Q-Tip's Beats 1 show "Abstract Radio" on December 11th, 2015.

title: You Again
desc: Reference track for "We Major" with Tony Williams. Also features different drums and some synths not present in the released version.

title: Common - They Say
desc: Leaked before Be released, features a Consequence verse rather than a Kanye feature.

title: Jennifer Lopez - Get Right
desc: Unreleased remix of Jennifer Lopez's 2005 track. Vocals are apparently identical the verse on Kanye's "Gone".

title: The Game - Dreams
desc: OG of The Game's "Dreams" from his album The Documentary. Includes entirely new finished verses. Leaked in 2011.

title: Barry Bonds [V2]
desc: Alternate version of "Barry Bonds" with a slightly different instrumental, alternate lyrics, and an open verse at the end. Finally leaked on March 21, 2022 with the Graduation Groupbuy Bundle.

title: Drunk N Hot Girls
desc: OG Filename: DRUNK N HOT GIRLS 2.24.07ADRUFF_03.aifAn early version of "Drunk And Hot Girls" featuring unfinished mumble vocals and more simplistic production. Made on February 24th, 2007. Finally leaked on March 21, 2022 with the Graduation Groupbuy Bundle. Leaked as an AIF file.

title: Everything I've Got [V1]
desc: Unreleased song featuring a verse and hook by Termanology.

title: Everything I've Got [V2]
desc: Version featuring an extra Kanye verse which was included on The Graduate mixtape.

title: Flashing Lights (Remix)
desc: Early remix from the Graduation EP featuring Pusha T and Malice. Clipse vocals were later used in "Mic Check".

title: Flashing Lights (Remix)
desc: Leaked remix featuring Raheem DeVaughn.

title: Good Life [V2]
desc: Seen being made in a youtube video. There are different drums and synths. Kanye is seen freestyling as the beat is being made.

title: Good Life [V3]
desc: OG Filename: GOODLIFE.aifAlternate instrumental and lyrics. Leaked as part of the Graduation Bundle on March 21, 2022.

title: Good Morning
desc: An older version of "Good Morning", rougher vocals are present in the snippet alongside less production than the released version.

title: Goodbye
desc: OG Filename: Goodbye 2.17.07 ADRUFF_03.aifOriginal version of "Good Night" with alternate lyrics and different instrumental. Made on February 17th, 2007. Leaked as part of the Graduation Bundle on March 21, 2022.

alts: (Can't Tell Me Nothing, I Get Money)
desc: Demo of "Can't Tell Me Nothing" with alternate instrumental and a Jeezy feature. Leaked as part of the Graduation Bundle on March 21, 2022.

title: Homecoming [V2]

title: I Wonder
desc: Alternate version of I wonder with different drums found in the Acapella bleed.

title: Story Begins [V1]
desc: OG Filename: STORY BEGINS.. RUFF 1.aifDemo of "Big Brother" with a Prince sample. Finally leaked on March 21, 2022 with the Graduation Groupbuy Bundle. Leaked as an AIF file.

title: Big Brother [V2]
desc: OG version featuring different lyrics. Snippets were included in a video posted to Tony Williams YouTube channel.

title: Stronger [V1]
desc: Early mix with an unreleased verse. Tagged.

title: Stronger [V2]
desc: OG Filename: Stronger Mike Dean Mix 9Early mix with final lyrics. Has minor beat differences.

desc: Remix made to promote the superbowl. Never got an official release.

title: Lil Wayne - Did It Before
desc: Kanye produced leaked cut from Tha Carter III sessions. Made in early 2007.

title: Mos Def - The Light Is Not Afraid Of The Dark
desc: Kanye produced throwaway from Mos Def's album True Magic. Previewed in 2006 and leaked in 2013.

title: Nicole Scherzinger - Loser
desc: Nicole Scherzinger song featuring Kanye; leaked in 2017. Recorded for her debut album in 2007.

title: T.I. - On Top Of The World
desc: Original version of the T.I. track featuring Kanye and B.o.B.

title: Amazing
feat: (feat. Young Jeezy, Mr Hudson & Tony Williams)
desc: OG Filename: 04-amazing-vlado-master-11_6bOG, unmastered file of "Amazing".

desc: OG Filename: Anyway Ref3 Main VladobounceOG version of "Paranoid" untagged. Mixing is very different, sounds like some different vocal takes. Less autotune and different intro on the verses.

title: HeartLess [V2]
desc: Unmastered leak of "Heartless".

title: Hot Sauce
desc: Small snippets of this fairly unknown track were played on Consequence's IG streams multiple times; from 808s & Heartbreak era. Song is a mumble demo, which was worked on a little further in the 808s & Heartbreak's sessions.

title: Love Lockdown [V2]

title: Robocop [V1]
desc: OG Filename: RobocopRef-Vlado_.Main_mp3OG version of "Robocop" leaked on the 12th anniversary of the album. Earlier instrumental than V2, but has mumble.

title: Robocop [V2]
desc: Same as V1 besides new vocals at 2:00-2:10, tagged

title: Robocop [V3]
desc: Percussion is mixed differently and the outro verse is absent.

title: Robocop [V7]
desc: Unreleased version of the song made for the music video. This version has different drums and is post 808s & Heartbreak's release. Likely made as a "New Mix" version of the song like other 808s & Heartbreak's tracks. Was scrapped after Amber and Kanye broke up. There are additional Tony Williams vocals.

title: Streetlights
desc: Music video version of the song, contains a different mix and additional Mr Hudson vocals.

title: Tell Everybody That You Know [V2]
desc: Seemingly the version that is released but Lil Wayne is not censored. The mixing and mastering is also not the same as released.

title: See You in My Nightmares [V3]
desc: Unreleased remix from the short film We Were Once A Fairytale. Referred to as "See You In My Nightmares (Bumptempo Squeak E. Clean Remix)". Only a low quality snippet from the movie was available for some time.

title: Welcome To Heartbreak [V2]
desc: Multiple beat differences, including the synths replacing the pianoand different drums. There are very small lyric changes also.

title: What It Is
desc: 808's era demo that was later given to Sophia Fresh as the song "What It Is". Was likely made just after the Graduation era for the early stages of Good Ass Job. T-Pain produced this track but the second verse remains unfinished.

title: Hard Horn Nightmare [V1]
desc: Version of the song from Winter Spring Summer Fall.

title: See Me Again [V1]
desc: Unfinished track leaked from just over a month before My Beautiful Dark Twisted Fantasy dropped. Rumoured to be for Winter Spring Summer Fall. Was leaked as "Never See Me Again", but current leakers who have the song confirm that the title is "See Me Again". Was rumored to interpolate "Futari Dake No Ceremony" by Yukiko Okada, but it really Interpolates "I Never Want To See You Again" by Quasi.

title: Summer Of Dreams
desc: Made in 2009 for the Winter Spring Summer Fall album. Was going to be reworked for Watch the Throne, but never was re-recorded. Snippet surfaced March 1st 2011, full version on the 2nd.

title: Eyes Closed
desc: Good Ass Job era throwaway; leaked in 2011. A version with Snoop Dogg was released on his album Doggumentary. Noted by lowkey to not be releasing, before it leaked.

title: Flashing Lights 2 [V1]
desc: Sequel to "Flashing Lights" from Graduation. The song was given to JYJ (KPOP group), while some of the production was reworked into Drake's "Find Your Love".

title: Good Friday
desc: Original version from G.O.O.D. Fridays.

title: Hard Horn Nightmare [V3]
desc: Solo Kanye version of Rick Ross's "Live Fast Die Young". Features backing vocals from Tony Williams and Connie Mitchell along with different lyrics than the other solo version. Sold on August 15th.

title: Hard Horn Nightmare [V4]
desc: Solo Kanye version of Rick Ross's "Live Fast Die Young". Features different lyrics than the other solo version. Long snippet leaked by Tuck, but it is not the full song as there is a fadeout that appears out of nowhere.

title: Hard Horn Nightmare [V5]
desc: Solo Kanye version of Rick Ross's "Live Fast Die Young". Snippet provided by leakth.is user DJ AssCheeks.

title: Hard Horn Nightmare [V6]
desc: Fully finished version with alternate Kanye verses and no mumble. Features Big Sean instead of Rick Ross and is 7:30 long. Snippet posted by DJ AssCheeks on leakth.is.

title: Rick Ross - Live Fast, Die Young [V7]
desc: Demo version of the Rick Ross song "Live Fast, Die Young".

title: Just Kill Me Please
desc: Untagged snippet of a throwaway mumble demo from 2009.

title: Mama's Boy [V2]
desc: Played during a Q-Tip Red Bull Interview. This version includes a different vocal take, and a slightly different instrumental using the same sample from the "Mama's Boy" that leaked.

title: POWER [V3]
desc: Unmastered leak using sample instead of interpolation like final version.

title: POWER [V4]
desc: Alternate version of "Power" that went up for sale. Contains noticeably louder drums than the final version. It is unknown when exactly this was made or whether there is any difference in the vocals.

title: Runaway [V2]
desc: Very early version of "Runaway" that has a different mix. Some of Kanye's vocals that are present in all other known versions of the song are seemingly missing in this version, meaning this is likely the earliest version of the song currently known.

title: Runaway [V3]
desc: Unfinished and unmastered leak.

title: See Me Again [V2]
feat: (feat. Bon Iver, Tony Williams, John Legend & Elly Jackson) (prod. Anthony Kilhoffer)
desc: OG Filename: See Me AK Edit 2.28.mp3File dated Feb 28, 2010. Later Version of "See Me Again" from Good Ass Job. Features Bon Iver, Tony Williams, John Legend and Elly Jackson vocals as well as additional production. Leaked by Jabba after he leaked his whole vault on October 2nd, 2022.

title: See Me Again [V3]
feat: (feat. Bon Iver, Tony Williams, John Legend & Elly Jackson)
desc: Later version of "See Me Again" with different drums, vocal effects and background vocal features. File rebounced in 2021.

title: See Me Now
desc: Leaked version without Big Sean's verse and with extra Kanye adlibs.

title: Shoot Up
desc: Unfinished track leaked in April 2019. Multiple reasons why this track is believed to be Good Ass Job era: Kanye worked with Bon Iver in 2009-2010 ("Monster" / "Lost in the World") Kanye worked with Santigold in 2009 ("Gifted") Beat was used officially in 2011 for B.o.B's "Shoot Up The Station".

title: So Appalled [V2]
desc: Leaked solo demo featuring an additional short Kanye verse.

title: Tragically Beautiful [V1]
desc: Original version of "Blame Game" with completely different lyrics and flow. Only similarity is the sample in the beat. Leaked alongside "Cruel Winter" and 2 BROCKHAMPTON songs.

Snippet from Good Ass Job era. Claimed by some to be "Diamonds & Dollars", however there is literally nothing to support this because it doesn't sound like "Diamonds & Dollars", isn't mixed like "Diamonds & Dollars", and the people who claim it is "Diamonds & Dollars" are not considered the best sources. It still might be "Diamonds & Dollars" though.

title: Christina Milian - Diamonds [V1]
desc: Solo Christina Milian version of the song recorded before Kanye hopped on the track.

title: Christina Milian - Diamonds [V2]
desc: Rough demo track Kanye recorded for Christina Milian after he happened to hear her song "Diamonds" due to them both using the same studio. Recorded after 808s & Heartbreak.

title: Christina Milian - Diamonds [V3]
desc: Version of "Diamonds" that features Kanye's demo vocals alongside Christina Milian's vocals. Found on some random mixtape that only includes a minute of the song.

title: Christina Milian - Diamonds [V4]
desc: Seemingly finished version of the song with a finished Kanye verse supposedly recorded the day after his original mumble demo. Christina Milian didn't end up using the song on her album so it was given to Teairra Marí.

title: Teairra Marí - Diamonds [V5]
desc: Teairra Marí version of "Diamonds" that was made after she bought the song from Milian's previous label after Milian left it. The album it was supposed to be on, At That Point, was shelved in 2010 due to so many of the songs leaking, including "Diamonds". The song did end up on Teairra's Don't Make Me Cause A Scene mixtape however the version on that mixtape was shorter than the leak. The Kanye verse is the same as the one on the Christina Milian version.

title: Drake - Forever
feat: (feat. Kanye West, Lil Wayne & Eminem) (prod. Boi-1da)
desc: Unmastered version of "Forever".

title: Kid Cudi - Erase Me
desc: Solo Cudi version of "Erase Me" with a rougher beat and a different vocal take on the hook. Being sold by Alek.

title: Kid Cudi - I Poke Her Face
desc: Original version of "Make Her Say" by Kid Cudi with earlier production by Kanye West.

title: Kid Cudi - Sky Might Fall
desc: Original version of the Kid Cudi track with earlier production by Kanye West.

title: Pharrell Williams - Diamonds & Dollars
desc: A snippet leaked by Music Mafia of a fairly unknown track featuring Kanye. Very likely made in 2009, when Pharrell released his sneakers with Diamonds & Dollars print. Most likely Pharrell's song due to his solo version demo of this song also being put up for sale by Music Mafia. Era is unconfirmed, but time line doesn't line up with 808s & Heartbreak.

title: Record4Hype
feat: (Good Ass Job, My Beautiful Dark Twisted Fantasy)
desc: Full zip file leaked in 2010, but was password protected for 10 years until, after a number of posts by Maker reinvigorating interest, an anonymous 4chan user found the master password to be "wewantmoney". The day after it was cracked, multiple articles came out about it, some with interviews from people involved. Files dated July 7, 2010.

title: Blame Game [V2]
desc: Solo demo leaked included within Record4Hype. The track has a rougher, unmixed vocal take for Kanye, as well as a beat that includes Aphex Twin's "Avril 14th" and not just an interpolation of it like the final release.

title: Dark Fantasy [V1]
desc: Found in Record4Hype.

title: Devil In A New Dress [V1]
feat: (Devil In A Blue Dress, Dean In A New Dress)
desc: Solo demo included within Record4Hype. Has a few mumble lines in Kanye's verses and is notably missing MIKE DEAN's guitar interlude and outro.

title: Ghetto University [V2]
desc: First snippet, from an Aug 6th, 2010 ustream. This version has nothing but Charlie Wilson vocals and the beat.

title: Ghetto University [V3]
desc: Version of "Ghetto University" included within Record4Hype. This version only includes Kid Cudi and Kanye's parts, with all other parts being filled with unfinished open verses. Includes a short skit at the end taken from the Musical - A New Brain.

title: Gorgeous [V2]
desc: "Gorgeous" demo found within Record4Hype. Kanye's vocals are a lot louder, with no Raekwon verse and a slightly different instrumental.

title: Hell Of A Life [V1]
desc: Includes alternate lyrics and a rough yet different take on the hook, same version included in the Record4Hype zip but untagged.

title: Holding Me Back

Track #10 on the original My Beautiful Dark Twisted Fantasy tracklist shared by Complex. Listed as bonus track by HipHopDX under name "Momma's Boyfriend".

"I'm In It" originally had insane guitar parts and felt more like a stadium song according to MIKE DEAN. According to Mike, he said that Rick Rubin, Noah Goldstein, and Kanye were the ones to strip back elements to make it more minimalistic. VC recording surfaced February 2022. Leaked by Jabba after he leaked his whole vault on October 2nd, 2022.

Was thought to be CyHi before the ref leaked.

desc: OG Filename: Bad Night-Tyga Ref BOUNCEA version with Tyga doing reference vocals for Kanye. File date confirms it is from 2015.

title: Bad Night [V6]
desc: Leaked in full on August 2nd, 2019 after a successful Groupbuy. Also known as "Bad Night" and "Capri-Sun". Has a more finished beat and lyrics compared to the other versions. Might've had a snippet released by Music Mafia at some point but it is unsure. Portions of the beat were reused for the "Hacker War Mission Music" from the Watch Dogs 2 Original Soundtrack in 2016.

title: Bad Night / Rap Tarantino [V7]
desc: One of four versions of the track. Owned by Music Mafia and BIZZLOW who released a tagged version of the song. Has a different instrumental and beatswitch with new lyrics. Samples "Petiatil Cx Htdui" by Aphex Twin at the end. Untagged version leaked in June 2021.

title: Can U Be [V3]
alts: (Get Off Me, Never Let Me Go, Waves, Clockwork Orange)
desc: Demo of "Waves", later than the Yeezus 2 version.

title: Can U Be [V4]
alts: (Get Off Me, Never Let Me Go, Waves, Clockwork Orange)
desc: Version of "Can U Be" played on the Glastonbury stage before Kanye's set. Was thought to have Drake or Big Sean by KTT users at the time, but it turned out to just be the sample.

title: Can U Be [V5]
alts: (Get Off Me, Never Let Me Go, Waves, Clockwork Orange)
desc: Previously owned by MusicMafia, who attempted a failed groupbuy for the song priced at 2 BTC. The refrain of this version is confirmed to have different lyrics from other "Can U Be" versions. "Never Let Me Go" is known to not be apart of this version.

title: Deja Vu
desc: Kanye mumbling over most of the beat. Likely made during the same sessions as "No More Parties in LA". Leaked in early June 2019.

title: Don't Jump [V1]
desc: Snippet previewed at Yeezy Season 2. The name of the song was said to be "Lowery", but this name was admitted to be fake by the person who reported it.

title: Don't Jump [V2]
desc: Almost certainly the same song as the Yeezy Season 2 snippet, but it lacks any shared vocals. This is a short track that contains short Kanye parts and a Kendrick Lamar verse. Sold and leaked along with "Liberated" by SpirDark. This is not the full version of the song since the leaker added a fade in and fade out. Likely the rest of the song is the parts of V1 that aren't included in this snippet.

title: Enya [V3]
desc: 13 minutes long freestyle that Post Malone did for "Enya" during his sessions with Kanye in mid-2015. Despite being labeled as a reference track his lyrics seem to be speaking from his own perspective, so it may have been intended to be cut down into a verse the way his "Fade" freestyle was. Samples "Return To Innocence" by Enigma.

title: Enya [V4]
desc: OG Filename: KW - Enya 11.30.15Version of "Enya" from late 2015 with Kanye doing the hook. Has slightly different instrumental to V3. Leaked October 3rd, 2022.

title: Fade [V3]
desc: Version of "Fade" heard in the background of a tweet from August 4, 2015. Snippet is instrumental only.

title: Fade [V6]
desc: Same intro, chorus, bridge and first verse as the released version but in the part where Kanye says "I love to... I wanna... I'm tryna..." on the final version he is mumbling. Post Malone freestyles for around 16 minutes, and his vocals used in the released version are taken from this freestyle. Likely recorded in the 2015 Post Malone and Kanye sessions.

title: Fade [V7]
desc: Features a different beat. Leaked in early 2016. Played at Yeezy Season 2.

title: Father Stretch [V1]
alts: (Father, Father Stretch My Hands Pt. 1, Liberated)
desc: Very early version of "Father Stretch My Hands Pt. 1" that features an earlier beat and Kanye mumbling. Features Caroline Shaw's vocals that were later used in "Pt. 2". Leaked with stems.

title: Liberated [V2]
alts: (Father, Father Stretch My Hands Pt. 1, Father Stretch)
desc: Original version of "Father Stretch My Hands" featuring Kendrick Lamar. Engineer did not include the full song, just Kendrick's verse and some Kanye vocals.

title: Father [V3]
alts: (Father Stretch, Father Stretch My Hands Pt. 1, Liberated)
desc: Version of "Father Stretch My Hands" played by Keyon Christ in a Discord VC. Has rougher and longer verse than the later versions. Some vocals from this version were reused for "Pt. 2". Seemingly no Kid Cudi feature.

title: FML [V3]
desc: First version of "FML" with Kanye vocals, containing a mumble verse and hook, and different production from other versions of the song. Leaked with stems after a successful groupbuy. Dated December 9, 2015. After the cutoff there is said to be a Travis verse, however it's unknown if that is a separate version.

title: FML [V4]
desc: Later version of "FML" with different Kanye vocals from the previous version, along with instrumental differences. No open verse. Dated January 6, 2016. Leaked after a blind groupbuy on May 6, 2022.

title: FML [V5]
desc: Version of "FML" that features Young Thug, unknown exactly when it was made but it uses the early SWISH version of the instrumental. Was played in a Che Pope livestream however a longer snippet from the livestream didn't surface until July 2022.

title: FML [V6]
feat: (feat. Travis Scott) (prod. Darren King & Hudson Mohawke)
desc: Version of "FML" around 5 minutes long that was likely cut down for the following version, featuring alt production and an open verse, along with a more energetic Kanye vocal take. Commonly referred to as the "Shogani" version, with how often he has played it in VC. Produced by Darren King. Leaked on May 26, 2022.

title: FML [V7]
desc: Reworked version of "FML" from January 2016. More finished re-recorded Kanye vocal take and different instrumental with Keyon production. Samples "Rückzug" by Vermont.

title: FML [V8]
desc: A version of "FML" leaked after a successful groupbuy in March 2022 with stems. Dated 1.17.16.

title: FML [V9]
desc: Newer version with The Weeknd replacing part of Kanye's mumble hook. Contains new drums and extended sample outro. Possibly dated 1.21.16.

title: FML [V10]
desc: This version seems to have additional vocals from The Weeknd as well as unidentified sample or feature on the outro. Unknown if Travis Scott is still featured as the snippet does not show enough.

title: Forever [V1]
desc: Snippet from backstage at Glastonbury 2015. Contrary to popular belief, this is a separate song from "Can U Be". The instrumental of this song was released by Keyon on his soundcloud under the title "Forever Mitus", and a solo version with vocals by JAYLIEN was officially released on an EP by Keyon Christ. Beat was originally meant for Rihanna on her 2016 album ANTI. The song title was confirmed when Keyon referred to the snippet that leaked with Kanye vox as "#Forever"

title: Fuck The Internet [V3]
desc: A 8-minute solo Post Malone freestyle over Kanye's beat which became "Fuck The Internet". A part of the 2015 Post Malone and Kanye sessions.

title: Post Malone - Fuck The Internet [V4]
desc: Demo version featuring an unfinished Kanye verse and hook. A version without Kanye leaked in 2018 and was released for Post Malone's 2019 album, Hollywood's Bleeding.

title: Travis Scott - Piss On Your Grave [V3]
desc: OG Filename: Travis Scott - Piss On Your Grave_02.mp3Leaked June 13, 2019. Was given to Travis at this point as they were found within Travis project files and are all featuring Kanye.

title: Travis Scott - Piss On Your Grave [V4]
desc: OG Filename: Travis Scott - Piss On Your Grave_03.mp3Leaked on July 27th, 2021. Has minor difference to the other one.

title: Travis Scott - Piss On Your Grave [V5]
desc: OG Filename: Travis Scott - Piss On Your Grave_04.mp3Leaked July 19, 2019. Later version of the song with finished Travis verse.

title: High Life [V2]
desc: A 2-minute solo Post Malone freestyle over an unknown Kanye song called "High Life". A part of the 2015 Post Malone and Kanye sessions.

title: Highlights [V3]
desc: Early version of "Highlights" with an unfinished verse, different bassline, and a more simplistic different instrumental.

title: Highlights [V4]
desc: Similar to previous version but with extra samples and some vocals and drums removed.

title: Highlights [V5]
feat: (feat. Tony Williams & Young Thug) (prod. Darren King)
desc: Version of "Highlights" with aditional production, drums & samples produced by Darren King. Leaked for free in April, 2022.

title: I Feel Like That [V6]
desc: Low quality audio leaked from Glastonbury 2015 stage setup. Later revealed to be Ty Dolla $ign and Tony Williams when the CDQ Snippet was leaked. Person who leaked the snippet said it was from 2016, however other people with the song confirmed it was the same as the version from Glastonbury.

title: The Mall [V2]
desc: A snippet from a 12-minute solo Post Malone freestyle over an unknown Kanye song from 2015 called "The Mall". A part of the 2015 Post Malone and Kanye sessions.

title: 2 Rihannas [V4]
desc: Played backstage at Glastonbury 2015 immediately after "Can U Be". The song contains some punch ins from Pusha T, and according to a trusted source, this was intended for Kanye's album, meaning it was no longer a reference track for Rihanna.

title: Rihanna - Mitus Touch [V5]
desc: J. Cole version of "Mitus Touch", a song meant for Rihanna.

title: Nina Chop [V3]
desc: A more finished demo of "Nina Chop" recorded either in late 2015 or early 2016. Has a different vocal take from Kanye with a "small mumble part" and "some other various diff parts such as extra samples".

title: No More Parties In LA [V2]
desc: Video of Kanye recording an early version of "No More Parties In LA". Thought to be from 2010, but was actually recorded in late 2015 as a photo from Ian Connor has been found with Kanye wearing the same outfit as the snippet.

title: Only [V1]
desc: Solo Kanye demo, initially called "Only". Was listed by Music Mafia for a time, but was never sold.

title: Only [V2]
desc: OG Filename: Only Ye Reference-TYGA.mp3Song name confirmed from OG filename. Most likely came from the same studio session as "Rich Nigga Drunk" and "Man Up". This is a more finished version compared to the other solo snippet of this song that leaked from Music Mafia. Tyga raps a verse intended for Kanye.

title: Only One [V5]
desc: Snippet released in the scrapped "Only One" game trailer. All longer versions are fan made. Possibly the version which appeared on an early SWISH tracklist, unconfirmed if Ty Dolla $ign's vocals are still present. Used as the outro of the Saint Pablo tour version of the song.

title: Real Friends [V1]
desc: Snippet posted on TheSource of an early version of "Real Friends" with songwriter LaShawn Daniels. Alek mistakenly said this was from 2015.

title: Real Friends [V2]
desc: Solo version with different Kanye parts in place of the Ty Dolla $ign feature, and has a slightly differing instrumental. Leaked on August 10th, 2020.

title: Rich Nigga Drunk
desc: OG Filename: Rich Nigga Drunk Ruff- BOUNCE.mp3SWISH era song made alongside all the other Tyga songs. It was sold by Music Mafia along with the other Tyga tracks. There might be other earlier versions of this song, but this is unconfirmed.

title: Sell Your Soul [V1]
desc: OG Filename: KW - Sell Your Soul Ref (8.15.15).mp3Version of "Sell Your Soul" without any Kanye vocals. Leaked alongside all other versions of the song on April 24th, 2022 after a successful groupbuy. Dated August 15th, 2015.

title: Sell Your Soul [V2]
desc: Assumed to be an interlude or an intro for the song "Souls". Leaked alongside all other versions of the song on April 24th, 2022 after a successful groupbuy.

title: Souls [V18]
desc: MIKE DEAN version of "Souls". The audio that is linked is somewhat innacurate, because there are many plugins that Mike Dean used in the production that could not be cracked.

title: Ultimate Lie [V5]
desc: Played by Che Pope on Instagram Live on October 22nd, 2020.

title: Ultralight Beams [V1]
desc: Early demo of "Ultralight Beam" recorded in early 2016, has different production, Chance parts and a completely different Kanye verse. Leaked in full on October 2nd, 2022.

title: WE FUCK [V1]
desc: SWISH version of "Freestyle 4". Contains alternate verses and MIKE DEAN production.

title: Fuck RT Now [V2]
desc: Snippet of original version with different lyrics. Most likely is a solo version, outro is open.

title: Freestyle 4 [V3]
desc: Played by Che Pope on Instagram Live on October 22nd, 2020. Possibly a reference track.

title: Wolves [V6]
desc: A VC recorded snippet of SWISH "Wolves" leaked on November 27th, 2021. Contains additional vocals from Caroline Shaw as well as new production, featuring an organ. Contains additional mumble Kanye vocals and alternate lines.

title: A$AP Ferg - Wolves and Robots
desc: A$AP Ferg throwaway made in 2015 produced by Kanye & Pharrell. Leaked on December 16th, 2020.

title: The Weeknd - Gone
alts: (Soul Dog, When I See It, Tell Your Friends, Tell Your Friends About It)
desc: A Weeknd song that uses lyrics that would later become a verse on "When I See It" / "Tell Your Friends". Previewed by High Klassified in July of 2015. The song leaked in full in May of 2016.

title: Young Thug - Code Red
desc: Solo Young Thug song produced by Kanye West. Had an unsuccessful groupbuy. Production of this matches the production of the outro to "Man Up V6", so it was probably made during the same time

title: Madlib Freestyles
desc: Very short snippets posted by Private on November 25th, 2019. Mostly Kendrick and Kanye messing about in the studio. 13 in total.

title: 30 Hours [V11]
feat: (Paper Thin Love, Paper Thin Lover, We Are, College Dorm Sweetheart)
desc: Different mix of the Soundcloud version of "30 Hours", had been circulated since 2016 but was only actually leaked in May 2022. Higher quality than the soundcloud version.

title: All We Got [V1]
desc: Kanye's freestyle of "All We Got". Contains no Chance vocals and was played by Chance during a Zane Lowe Beats 1 interview.

title: Chance the Rapper - All We Got [V2]
feat: (feat. Kanye West) (prod. Kanye West & The Social Experiment)
desc: Similar to the previous version, but with additional production. Chance has very minor vocals at the start of the song, however the rest is open until Kanye's mumble freestyle.

title: Chance the Rapper - All We Got [V3]
feat: (feat. Kanye West) (prod. Kanye West & The Social Experiment)
desc: Original mix of Kanye's vocals and 0.13 seconds shorter than the official release. Originally leaked in May 2016 along with the whole mixtape, and rediscovered by u/ghost_bubbles in September 2020.

title: Bad Night [V8]
desc: A version of "Bad Night" produced by DJDS with a more emotionally driven instrumental. It is unknown when it is from, however it is likely The Life Of Pablo due to his "I Feel Like That" version being that era too. Leaked by Jabba on October 2nd, 2022.

title: Come And Go
desc: Lil Uzi Vert reference track. Uzi used parts of the hook for the chorus on Rambo Savage’s 2018 song "That’s on You". Leaked in 2016.

title: Fade [Yeezy Season 3 Version]
desc: Yeezy Season 3 remix combining elements of earlier verisons.

title: Nina Chop [V4]
feat: (ref. Chance the Rapper) (feat. Rihanna & Swizz Beatz)
desc: Reference track Chance made for "Famous." Played by Chance alongside his "Waves" reference on a Zane Lowe Beats 1 interview. Has completely different instrumental.

title: Famous [V5]
desc: Mumble demo of "Famous" played by ConsTV in November 2020, has a differently structured Rihanna hook and some possible minor mixing differences on the instrumental.

title: Famous [V6]
desc: "Famous" OG that doesn't seem to have many differences besides a shortened Rihanna hook.

title: Father [V4]
feat: (ref. Kanye West) (feat. Kid Cudi) (prod. Metro Boomin)
alts: (Father Stretch, Father Stretch My Hands Pt. 1, Liberated)
desc: Original version with different instrumental and some early mumble verses. Features Kanye beatboxing drums. Has a part that is similar to the 2 Chainz snapchat snippet. Full partially tagged CDQ leaked by Saint Ra1nbow. Leaked without tags in August 2022.

title: Father [V5]
feat: (ref. Kanye West) (feat. Kid Cudi & Kelly Price) (prod. Metro Boomin)
alts: (Father Stretch, Father Stretch My Hands Pt. 1, Liberated)
desc: Original version with different instrumental and some early mumble verses. Has a part that is similar to the 2 Chainz snapchat snippet. Different/more complete version of the Father leaked by Saint due to Kelly Prices vocals being barely able to be heard after the first verse at 1:40.

title: Father [V6]
feat: (ref. Kanye West) (feat. Kid Cudi) (prod. Metro Boomin)
alts: (Father Stretch, Father Stretch My Hands Pt. 1, Liberated)
desc: Snippet of a demo from 2 Chainz' Snapchat. Has a part similar to "Father" although it's extended a bit longer. Has Kid Cudi vocals over the open beatbox instrumental. Recorded January 29th.

title: Father Stretch My Hands [V7]
alts: (Father Stretch My Hands Pt. 1, Father Stretch, Liberated, Father, Pt. 2, Panda)
desc: Version of the song featuring a different mix than the final and more of the sample at the beginning of the song. Contains both parts of the song. Part 1 is longer than the final version and Part 2 contains an open verse, the full track is over 6 minutes long.

title: Father Stretch My Hands Pt. 1 [V8]
desc: Snippet of a scrapped verse from CyHi the Prynce.

title: FML [V11]
desc: Further along version with no Travis Scott vocals and reused instrumental parts from the SWISH versions of "FML". Slightly tagged version released by Music Mafia on May 1st 2018.

title: Freestyle 4 [V4]
desc: Early version with finished verse but with Kanye singing Desiigner's hook. From the livestream of The Life of Pablo Kanye did upon release.

title: Freestyle 4 (Remix)
desc: Remix leaked tagged by MusicMafia, with the full untagged version leakedby Alek on January 31st, 2020.

title: Highlights [V6]
desc: Appears to be further along in production. Beat sounds almost doneand has less Kanye mumbling.

title: I Feel Like That [V7]
desc: OG Filename: IFLT - DJDS FULL SONG @ 110.m4aVersion of "I Feel Like That" from The Life Of Pablo. The OG File's metadata labels it as the "TLOP DJDS VERSION". Was commonly referred to as "Shogani IFLT," as he played it a lot in VCs. Leaked by Jabba on October 2nd, 2022.

title: Madlib Freestyle 6
desc: Rumoured to be part of the "40 tracks" Ye and Kendrick recorded together during The Life of Pablo era.

title: No More Parties in L.A. [V3]
feat: (feat. Kendrick Lamar) (prod. Kanye West, Kevin Smith, Robert Bisel, Ricardo Kim, & Madlib)
desc: "No More Parties In LA" OG file. Might be an alt mix.

title: Real Friends (Remix)
desc: A remix leaked by Music Mafia with an unreleased DMX verse.

title: Revenge / Pop Style
desc: Two demos created in the same vocal session. These demos feature Kanye adlibs and mumbles. Song sessions confirm that these two songs are not edited together but instead just recorded at the same time. "Pop Style" demo starts when there's about 1:06 left. Likely made for their joint project Wolves (Calabasas Is The New Abu Dhabi). Recorded in late January (20-29) but is not confirmed what day it specifically was.

title: Saint Pablo [V4]
desc: Played at The Art of Hustle release party, featuring a different verse from Sampha. Leaked March 31st, 2016.

title: Spread My Wings
desc: The Life Of Pablo throwaway titled "Spread My Wings". Little is known about this song, however it features no Kanye vocals with the feature on the track doing the whole song. Part of a The Life Of Pablo album zip. Dated February 2nd, 2016.

title: Ultralight Beam (Remix)
desc: Was being sold by Spir at one point. Apparently a remix of the song, probably made alongside his remix of "Freestyle 4".

title: Waves [V5]
desc: Original version leaked in early 2016. Samples "Return To Innocence" by Enigma.

title: Waves [V6]
desc: Reference track Chance made for "Waves". Played by Chance alongside his "Famous" reference on a Zane Lowe interview. that features a choir driven beat, and in the second half has a beat resembling "Enya." This version was also performed by Chance live at several shows. Possibly owned by Spirdark.

title: Waves [V7]
desc: Went up for sale on June 19, 2022. Not the same as the version Chance played for Zane Lowe. For some reason, this version incorporates "Father Stretch My Hands" in the outro.

title: Waves [V8]
desc: Version with an alternate synth-based beat that leaked in 2019.

title: Alicia Keys - In Common [V2]
desc: Leak with an alternate Instrumental.

title: Alicia Keys - In Common (Remix)
feat: (feat. Kanye West & Travis Scott) (prod. Travis Scott, MIKE DEAN & Illiago)
desc: Version of Alicia Keys' "In Common" with a Travis Scott feature and different production from him and MIKE DEAN. The song was previewed on .WAV RADIO but never released and the original file later leaked without censored vocals or .WAV RADIO tags.

title: Consequence - Fade (Remix)
desc: Remix by Consequence, made in The Life of Pablo era but using the early SWISH version instrumental. Unknown if Ty Dolla $ign or Post Malone are still featured. Probably not an official remix.

title: Consequence - Famous (Remix)
desc: Remix by Consequence. Previewed in 2020 by ConsTV live on Instagram. Probably not an official remix.

title: Consequence - Feedback (Remix)
desc: Remix by Consequence. Previewed in 2020 by ConsTV live on Instagram. Uses the Yeezus II "Feedback" instrumental. Probably not an official remix.

title: Freddie Gibbs - Evil Eye
desc: A Freddie Gibbs song that was cut from Bandana, uses the same beat as one of the Kendrick x Kanye x Madlib freestyles.

title: Future - In Abundance
desc: Intended for Future's mixtape Purple Reign without Kanye's verse, but it wasn't included on the official mixtape. Kanye verse was rerecorded for the song "Bipolar", which became "Go2DaMoon". Full song leaked on 2/22/21.

title: PARTYNEXTDOOR - I Hope
desc: A unreleased song made by PND that shares the same beat as "Glow". This track is not related to the Kanye & Drake song "Glow" in any way besides the beat. Snippets were released by PRIVATEFRIEND before the song eventually leaked on 8/29/20.

title: Kid Cudi - Maple [V1]
desc: Uses the same beat as "All Eyes On Ye". Mainly just Cudi mumbling. Unknown if it was made before or after "All Eyes On Ye", but may be earlier as the beat is a bit simpler.

title: All Eyes On Ye [V2]
desc: Features mumbling from Kanye and a synth based beat. Has a somewhat more developed beat as a leaked Kid Cudi song called "Maple".

title: Can U Be [V7]
alts: (Never Let Me Go, Waves, Clockwork Orange, Get Off Me)
desc: A trusted source has stated that TurboGrafx16 version of "Can U Be" exists, specifically the version played by Che Pope with Travis Scott. However, it's possible that this version is from The Life Of Pablo.

title: Euro 2 [V1]
desc: Solo Kanye version. Leaked after producer TM88 got hacked.

title: A$AP Rocky - Euro 2 [V2]
desc: Full untagged leak. Song structure is different from the Music Mafia leak. Portions of the track don't feature vocals with minor effects differences. Song was given to Rocky, proven by the original filename.

title: Face Down [V1]
desc: Solo version of "Face Down", original snippet posted by Music Mafia. Leaked after a successful groupbuy on December 3rd, 2020.

title: Hold Tight [V2]
desc: Full high quality version released by Music Mafia. Formerly known as "Black Tron". Snippets of the song were previewed by Young Thug and Migos shortly after the release of The Life of Pablo, possibly making it one of the first songs recorded for TurboGrafx16.

title: Hold Tight [V3]
desc: Snippet surfaced before the leak of V1. Only noticeable difference is that Quavo's vocals are autotuned and reverbed.

title: No Reason [V1]
desc: Leaked fully in early November 2018 by iTagen. This version is 1:50 longer compared to the other version that leaked and features different verses.

title: Post Malone - No Reason [V2]
desc: Leaked in August 2018 by SomeRandomNob. Doesn't include Kanye's verse as this song was planned for Post's first album, Stoney, before being scrapped.

title: Rap Tarantino [V9]
desc: Snippet of a solo version produced by DJ Carnage. This version is the only one that was intended for TurboGrafx16. The verses are finished and the hook remains the same as other versions.

title: Rap Tarantino [V10]
desc: Later version of DJ Carnage's "Rap Tarantino" featuring a different drum pattern and sample on the verses.

title: Saint Pablo [V3]
desc: Produced by Keyon Christ (Mitus). Features some alternate lyrics from Sampha in the final verse. Likely the version meant for TurboGrafx16 but this is unconfirmed. Leaked on June 19th, 2019.

title: Spaceships [V1]
desc: OG Filename: Spaceship_ref 03.19.17.mp3Snippet leaked on June 11th, 2021. Probably recorded alongside "Champions" and "Castro".

title: Post Malone - Don't Act Like You Care
desc: OG FIlename: Don't Act Like You Care (Super Rough 2) (feat - Kanye West).mp3Leaked fully in late June 2019 after a successful Groupbuy. Very similar vibe to "No Reason", so it's probably same sessions too.

title: Theophilus London - Lovers King
desc: Two snippets featuring Kanye production and Theophilus vocals. This song is on a tracklist for Theophilus' scrapped album that was announced summer 2016.

title: Tyga - Feel Me
desc: Features one different line than the released version

title: ??? [V3]
feat: (with Kanye West, Gucci Mane, Big Sean, 2 Chainz, Travis Scott, Yo Gotti, Quavo & Desiigner)
desc: Recording of the original production by Menace. Uploaded in 2017 by the producer. Any snippets of this version are likely lost. A fake edit from Logan Smitherman that recreates the production leaked in 2018.

title: Champions [V4]
feat: (with Kanye West, Gucci Mane, Big Sean, 2 Chainz, Travis Scott, Yo Gotti, Quavo & Desiigner)
desc: Original version from it's debut on Real 92.3. Slightly earlier mix than the final, with less effects on the synth, harder hitting drums and less brickwalling. Was leaked in low quality a few days later. "Champions" is from the 2016 version of Cruel Winter, as opposed to the 2013 version

title: Champions [V5]
feat: (with Kanye West, Gucci Mane, Big Sean, 2 Chainz, Travis Scott, Yo Gotti, Quavo & Desiigner)
desc: Version dated 9-2-16, so likely the version planned for the Cruel Winter album. Leaked with the multitrack stems as a bonus for "This Is The Glory". Very similar to V4, but Quavo is only on there once, along with some alternate mixing changes.

title: Face Down [V4]
desc: Solo 070 Shake version. Likely recorded by her during Cruel Winter sessions

title: Face Down [V5]
feat: (with Kanye West, 070 Shake & Desiigner) (prod. Metro Boomin & Keyon Christ)
desc: Made during 2016 Cruel Winter sessions. Features verses from all three and a Metro Boomin tag similar to the Lil Yachty & Quavo version. Leaked in March 2022 after a successful groupbuy.

title: Panda (G.O.O.D. Music Remix) [V1]
desc: Demo version of the G.O.O.D. Music "Panda" remix that features Sia vocals. Features unfilled open verses. Leaked by Alek.

title: The Weeknd - All I Know [V1]
feat: (feat. Kanye West & The-Dream) (prod. Cashmere Cat, The Weeknd & Ben Billions)
desc: Shorter version with just The Weeknd, The-Dream and Kanye vocals.

title: The Weeknd - All I Know [V2]
feat: (feat. Kanye West, The-Dream, Big Sean & Quavo) (prod. Cashmere Cat, The Weeknd & Ben Billions)
desc: Leaked demo of the Weeknd's song from his album Starboy. Kanye's vocals are still unfinished in this version. Big Sean and Quavo are now featured. Likely recorded during Cruel Winter/TurboGrafx16 sessions. Leaked in April 2019.

title: The Weeknd - All I Know [V3]
feat: (feat. Kanye West, The-Dream, Big Sean & Quavo) (prod. Cashmere Cat, The Weeknd & Ben Billions)
desc: Features a more finished sounding version of Kanye's verse. Said by Music Mafia to have the same features as the earlier version.

title: Again
desc: Snippet posted by LilGoblin on TheSource. Listed as being from 2017 and being 1:32 long. Seller notes it's a mumble demo. Currently not for sale.

title: Bottom Line
desc: Snippet posted by LilGoblin on TheSource. Listed as being from 2017 and being 2:41 long. Samples "Bottom Line" by Electric Wire Hustle. Seller notes it's a mumble demo. Currently not for sale.

title: Brothers [V3]
